text:
We discovered the place in search of Vietnamese food.

This place is one of the nice coffee shops in Bukit Batok area. It offers wide variety of good quality cuisines, home made drinks are also good.

The price is competitive.

One thing they can improve is the smoking area, seems like it is not well isolated.

Similar concept to Kopitiam. There are about 10 to 11 stalls seeking different kinds of food including Korean BBQ, Vietnamese food and also HK roast Meat. Pretty contemporary in terms of such international food being available in a coffee shop. Food taste good.

Longstanding food court in the area. There are appoximately 12 stalls comprising halal and non-halal food. Drinks stall opens early in the morning. There are plenty of seatings, about 120 pax (all indoor porched with ceiling fans).
Michael’s rojak recently moved from Block 113 Jurong East Central… go have his rojak, it’s really affordable and delicious :D The sauce is really lovely.

Nice western food
